This endpoint is used by *sellers* to notify marketplaces that the price has changed for one of their SKUs. 

There is no request body in this call, indicating the new price value, for instance. It only notifies a specific marketplace (`accountName`) that a seller (`sellerId`) has changed the price of an SKU (`skuId`). 

*Marketplaces* will then call the [fulfillment endpoint](https://developers.vtex.com/vtex-rest-api/reference/fulfillment-simulation) provided in the seller registration form to get the updated price information.
data.description_suggestion: Notifies a marketplace that a seller has updated the price for a specific SKU. This endpoint triggers a price change notification without requiring a request bodythe new price value is retrieved by the marketplace through the fulfillment endpoint. The seller specifies the marketplace (`accountName`), their seller ID (`sellerId`), and the affected SKU ID (`skuId`). Upon successful notification, the marketplace can then call its fulfillment endpoint to fetch the updated price information. This operation does not modify data directly but initiates an asynchronous update process.

The email template is customizable through the marketplace's VTEX Admin Message Center. Returns the created seller lead object with ID, creation date, and last update date. This operation initiates the seller onboarding process.

data.current_description:
This endpoint is triggered by the seller onboarding wizard, once the seller confirms their invitation. It can be used by marketplace operators to manually accept seller leads, and carry on with their onboarding process. 

Note that there's no specific API call that allows status changes. The operations only allow the seller lead to move forward: 

 From `invite` > to `Accept` > closing on `[Create seller](https://developers.vtex.com/docs/api-reference/marketplace-apis/#put-/seller-register/pvt/seller-leads/-sellerLeadId-/seller)`. 

If you want to change the status, you can start the process again, by deleting that lead through the *[Delete seller lead](https://developers.vtex.com/docs/api-reference/marketplace-apis/#delete-/seller-register/pvt/seller-leads/-sellerLeadId-)* endpoint, and resending the invite through the *[Resend seller lead's Invite](https://developers.vtex.com/docs/api-reference/marketplace-apis/#put-/seller-register/pvt/seller-leads/-sellerLeadId-/status)* endpoint.

Returns the updated seller lead object with the new `accepted` status. After acceptance, use the Create Seller endpoint to complete account provisioning.
